ine configuration is complete. So, executing the context in a deferred manner might be the solution.\n[thinking] \n[assistant-event] thinking_end\n[tool-call] start id=unknown\n[tool-call] delta {\"path\":\"tests/src/io.ktor/ktor-server-netty-jvm/3.2.0/src/test/kotlin/io_ktor/ktor_server_netty_jvm/NettyHttp2HandlerTest.kt\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"            assertThat(result.rootReceived.await(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS)).isTrue()\\n            assertThat(result.pushedReceived.await(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS)).isTrue()\\n            result.failure.get()?.let { throw AssertionError(\\\"HTTP/2 client failed\\\", it) }\\n\",\"newText\":\"            result.failure.get()?.let { throw AssertionError(\\\"HTTP/2 client failed\\\", it) }\\n            assertThat(result.rootReceived.await(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS)).isTrue()\\n            result.failure.get()?.let { throw AssertionError(\\\"HTTP/2 client failed\\\", it) }\\n            assertThat(result.pushedReceived.await(10, TimeUnit.SECONDS)).isTrue()\\n            result.failure.get()?.let { throw AssertionError(\\\"HTTP/2 client failed\\\", it) }\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"    override fun handlerAdded(context: ChannelHandlerContext) {\\n        Http2StreamChannelBootstrap(context.channel())\\n            .handler(ResponseBodyHandler(result.rootBody, result.rootReceived, result))\\n            .open()\\n            .addListener { future ->\\n                if (!future.isSuccess) {\\n                    result.fail(future.cause())\\n                    return@addListener\\n                }\\n\\n                val streamChannel: Http2StreamChannel = future.getNow() as Http2StreamChannel\\n                val headers: DefaultHttp2Headers = DefaultHttp2Headers().apply {\\n                    method(HttpMethod.GET.asciiName())\\n                    scheme(HttpScheme.HTTPS.name())\\n                    authority(\\\"127.0.0.1:$port\\\")\\n                    path(\\\"/\\\")\\n                }\\n                streamChannel.writeAndFlush(